A further error by a dispatcher, who misheard the classic car's VIN number, led to the vehicle wrongly being identified as stolen from California.

'I turned and looked back and saw three gun barrels pointed at me,' Mr Bruins from Washington told KLAS.

'And, obviously it hit me. Whoa! What's going on here. To this day I have never experienced anything like looking down the barrel of guns like that.'

The whole incident was recorded by the dashboard camera on the Highways officers.

In the footage the armed officers can be heard shouting over one another as they fire multiple commands at a bemused Mr Bruins.

At one point the confused senior citizen asked: 'Are you talking to me?'

